{
    "question_stem": "The functions f(x) = x\\(^2\\) - 4 and g(x) = 2x - 1 are defined for all real values of x. ",
    "parts": [
        {
            "part_label": "a",
            "question_text": "State the coordinates of the points where the graphs of y = f(x) and y = g(x) intersect.",
            "solution_text": "To find the points of intersection, we set f(x) = g(x):\n\\(x^2 - 4 = 2x - 1\\)\n\\(x^2 - 2x - 3 = 0\\)\n\\((x-3)(x+1) = 0\\)\nSo x = 3 or x = -1.\nWhen x = 3, y = f(3) = 3\\(^2\\) - 4 = 5, and y = g(3) = 2(3) - 1 = 5. Thus, (3, 5) is a point of intersection.\nWhen x = -1, y = f(-1) = (-1)\\(^2\\) - 4 = -3, and y = g(-1) = 2(-1) - 1 = -3. Thus, (-1, -3) is a point of intersection.\nThe points of intersection are (3, 5) and (-1, -3)."
        }
